e. Varma shows how occupation creates worlds of disrupted meaning in which clinical life is connected to political disorder, subverting biomedical neutrality, ethics, and processes of care in profound ways. By highlighting the imbrications between humanitarianism and militarism and between care and violence, care is theorized not as a redemptive practice, but as a fraught sphere of action that is never quite what it seems.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aCivil-military relationszIndiazJammu and Kashmir. 0aMilitary occupationxPsychological aspects. 0aPsychiatric clinicszIndiazJammu and Kashmir. 0aWar victimsxMental health serviceszIndiazJammu and Kashmir. 0aWar victimsxMental healthzIndiazJammu and Kashmir. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aefficacy of care.  apsychological trauma.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069631808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478012511zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478012511423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478012511/original  a978-3-11-069631-8  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEB